## Agent final message

> The query has been written to `query80.preql` and runs successfully. It produces 100 rows with the following structure:
> 
> **Query logic:**
> - **Imports:** `raw.all_sales` (multi-channel model combining store, catalog, and web sales/returns)
> - **Filters:**
>   - Date range: `2000-08-23` to `2000-09-22` on sale date
>   - Items with `current_price > 50`
>   - Promotions with `channel_tv = 'N'`
>   - Only sales whose outlet (store/catalog_page/web_site) is recorded (`channel_dim_text_id is not null`)
> - **Derived fields:**
>   - `outlet_label` — constructed with `case` to prefix the outlet's business code: `'store' || store.text_id`, `'catalog_page' || catalog_page.text_id`, or `'web_site' || web_site.text_id`
>   - `channel_label` — `'store channel'`, `'catalog channel'`, or `'web channel'`
> - **Metrics** (with `by rollup channel_label, outlet_label`):
>   - `sales` = `sum(ext_sales_price)`
>   - `returns` = `sum(coalesce(return_amount, 0))` — treating missing as zero
>   - `profit` = `sum(net_profit - coalesce(return_net_loss, 0))` — net profit minus matched return net loss
> - **Order:** channel_label then outlet_label, both `asc nulls first`
> - **Limit:** 100 rows
> 
> **Output (100 rows, grand total + channel subtotals + per-outlet rows):**
> - Row 1: grand total (null, null) — $13,560,113.88 sales, $692,603.11 returns, -$3,597,547.40 profit
> - Row 2: catalog channel subtotal (catalog channel, null) — $4,655,990.73 sales
> - Rows 3+: per-outlet rows for catalog_page, store, and web_site (sorted alphabetically)

